sublevels.theory:
**Iterators** provide a uniform way to traverse containers:
```cpp
std::vector<int> v = {1,2,3,4,5};
for (auto it = v.begin(); it != v.end(); ++it) {
    std::cout << *it;
}
```

**STL algorithms** work with iterators:
```cpp
#include <algorithm>
std::sort(v.begin(), v.end());
auto it = std::find(v.begin(), v.end(), 3);
std::count_if(v.begin(), v.end(), [](int x){ return x > 2; });
```

**`std::deque`** — double-ended queue, O(1) push/pop at both ends.
**`std::priority_queue`** — max-heap by default.
